{
  "doc_id": "39497",
  "text": "Following the extraction of essential oils that are intended for biological assay, a portion of essential oils were subjected to thin-layer chromatography (pre coated Silica gel G60F254) finger print analyses. Wagner and Bladts' procedure for plant drug analysis was used for the developing of chromatogram and for the identification of major secondary metabolites responsible for biological activity [CITATION_1] .",
